{
  "texts": [
    "However, When the scene's structure and spatial arrangements are uniformly distributed, methods based on low-level features can yield good results, but they are limited in complicated scenarios.Mid-level features methods aim to learn a set of fundamental functions used for feature encoding, such as the bag of visual words (BoVW) mode.",
    "However, such approaches have drawbacks, including severe quantization errors that might result in the loss of crucial information.",
    "As a result, many feature coding approaches have been suggested to make better use of spatial information, including spatial pyramid matching (SPM), probabilistic latent semantic analysis (pLSA), and improved Fisher kernel (IFK).",
    "Both low-level and mediumlevel features-based techniques rely mostly on hand-crafted features, limiting their versatility and applicability to a wide range of applications.High-level feature-based strategies such as deep learning have recently received more attention in computer vision, and major advances in remote sensing image classification based on deep features have been accomplished.",
    "Deep learning approaches outperform strategies based on low-level and mid-level features since the convolutional neural network (CNN) can automatically acquire more abstract and discriminative semantic information."
  ]
}